    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-idr-bgp-bfd-strict-mode-06.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-idr-bgp-bfd-strict-mode-06.txt</link>
        <title>"BGP BFD Strict-Mode", Mercia Zheng, Acee Lindem, Jeffrey Haas, Albert Fu</title>
        <dc:date>2021-11-08T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>This document specifies extensions to RFC4271 BGP-4 that enable a BGP speaker to negotiate additional Bidirectional Forwarding Detection (BFD) extensions using a BGP capability.  This BFD capability enables a BGP speaker to prevent a BGP session from being established until a BFD session is established.  It is referred to as BGP BFD "strict- mode".  BGP BFD strict-mode will be supported when both the local speaker and its remote peer are BFD strict-mode capable.</description>
    </item>
